                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.77/102½.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 515.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-08-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 31, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 820 of the
                    16th instant, enclosing a translation of an extract from Mr., Jaime Gurza’s book
                    entitled “Railroad Policy of the Government.”</p>
                <p>The Department will be glad to have you send it two copies of the work
                    mentioned.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.],</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
